	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If I remember correctly, &quot;Access denied&quot; in the Win9x days implies that something else has the file open for writing.<br /><br />If you have a @ECHO OFF at the top of your batch file, remove it, and you'll be able to tell what specifically is causing the error.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
